        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 13 at 2:31PM EDT by NWS Albany NY</headline>
        <description>At 231 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Athens, or over Hudson, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hudson, Catskill, Chatham, Claverack, Copake, Coxsackie, Athens,
Austerlitz, Philmont, Lorenz Park, Claverack-Red Mills, Cairo, Ghent,
Stockport, Stuyvesant, Hillsdale, Taghkanic, Burden Dock, Churchtown,
and Rossman.

This includes Interstate 87 between exits 21 and 21B.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
